article_title: ADM Boosts Dividend 26%, to Buy Back 18 Million Shares
article_text:
Archer Daniels Midland Co. raised its dividend by 26%, just after the U.S. grain trader and processor was blocked from a $2.7 billion deal for GrainCorp Ltd.

The company raised its quarterly dividend to 24 cents a share from 19 cents, with the increase costing ADM an extra $33 million a quarter. The company cited its strong cash flow and...
